<Author>Marie Jonathan
<Content>Lavish Hotel - Great Location We stayed at the Westin Palace Hotel in Madrid from December 5th to December 8th. We booked the room through Hotwire for 125.00 Euros per night. Upon checking in, we were informed that we were not entitled to a room with either a king size bed or two twin beds. We therefore had to pay an additional 50.00 Euros per night in order to get a room that had two beds. Our total price paid was 175.00 Euros per night and we were booked into an Executive Room.Our large room looked out over the traffic circle and fountain at Plaza Canovas del Castillo. It was very clean and in very good condition. The beds were extremely comfortable and had very nice sheets and down comforters. The bath room had a very nice shower with three shower heads to choose from, but there was no bath tub. During our entire vacation, this was the only hotel room that was nicer than our bedroom at home. That was important to us.The public spaces within the hotel are gorgeous. (However, please note that at the time we stayed there they we having a photo exhibit that feature photos taken within the hotel. While all of the photos well done and very tasteful, they all featured either partial or full frontal female nudity. That may or may not be an issue for you if you have kids in tow.)We arrived by car during the busy Friday afternoon commute. The doorman was very understanding and accommodating at our arrival. He allowed us to parking our car in the main drive way for over 10 minutes while we checked in.The hotel is in a perfect location. We did not have to take a taxi the entire time we were in Madrid because this hotel is within walking distance of everything that one would want to visit.Our only complaints were the following:The price of the food in the hotel restaurant as well as room service was the highest we have ever seen in our entire life. $25 for an ala carte hot dog is just simply outrageous. $43 for a continental breakfast is not justified. (Just around the corner and within the same building is the VIP Caf茅 that serves an entire meal for two with a bottle of wine for less than $50.)The staff of the hotel concierge needs to have some training in customer service. I am not sure of the reason, but they were curt in every interaction that we had with them. 
