<Content>Great Location but you pay for it We stayed at the Palace three times during our visit to Spain and found the rooms to be quite different depending on the location. We were on the SPG level twice and were happy with the rooms. The first room on the SPG level was on a courtyard and very quiet with comfortable beds. The next room was upgraded to a city view on the 4th floor with a step out balcony with a view of the fountain. It was not as quiet and the bed was very soft and uncomfortable. We did not realize until late a night and were given a bed board (who knew these still existed?) and it was ok after that. The closet and the fixtures were also not as nice as our first room. The last room was what they considered to but an upgraded 鈥渃ity view鈥?room on the 6th floor. If I paid up for windows that were above chest level I would have been disappointed but it was a fine room with the better beds and fixtures. The front desk staff was very nice but quite slow at times and we were happy that twice we got express check out forms so we did not have to wait (perhaps only for spg since we did not get it on the other floor). The breakfast was fine but when it was not included in our rate it was not remotely worth 28 euros for each person when you are paying in USD. I know it is because our currency issues but still it seemed high for what you were offered. We visited the VIPS around the corner a few times for snacks and drinks. It was very convenient. We loved the location for proximity to the museums, Retiro, Plaza Mayor, and Atocha but did not think the concierge was very good. We got bad information from them on 2 occasions regarding opening times. 
