<Author>Torero
<Content>Perfect Stay with a Captain on Board This was our second stay at the Westin Palace in three weeks and because we noted an improvement in various aspects we thought it was appropriate to write new comments about this property.If you have ever wondered if TripAdvisor comments are of any use then believe it. At the Palace there is a Captain on board, the General Manager. How do I know? Well, after my previous stay I wrote a review in TripAdvisor. I stated some problems we had, but that weren't bad enough to complain to the Hotel Management directly. Turns out the Palace has a service monitoring TripAdvisor comments and it also appears the General Manager makes an effort to correct flaws when he spots them. When we arrived on our most recent stay, we were greeted with apologetic comments regarding our previous stay (A note had been posted on our computer file) and we can honestly say this time all was perfect. Not only that, but we had found a great Easter deal on the hotel website for a deluxe double with breakfast for 245 鈧?/night.Service from all staff members was attentive and impeccable. Yes, at times it seamed they were overburdened. Despite this, they did their best to satisfy every request ASAP. The breakfast buffet in the Rotonda was plentiful with a great choice of foods for all tastes, American, European and local. One criticism here regarding the Orange juice. It tasted as if the skin had been squeezed with the pulp, much too bitter for us. We also visited the Gym on the 6th Floor. It is quite large with wonderful equipment. The Westin Palace is a non smoking hotel in its public areas. There is a lounge reserved for those who wish to indulge in smoking while enjoying a cocktail. There are many meeting rooms available for business events. The property is extremely luxurious and very well kept. The rooms are spotless, spacious and very comfortable. I just wish the internet connection were included.The closest Metro Station is not Atocha or Sol as mentioned in a previous review but Banco de Espa帽a. As you exit the Hotel, cross the avenue San Jeronimo and take the street right across called Marques de Cuba. The metro is at the end of that street on Calle Alcala, about three minutes away.Based on location, property and service, the Westin Palace is a wonderful treat you can offer yourself. And remember there is a captain on Board so if you run into any difficulties try mentioning it to staff members at reception and concierge, for I am convinced that management policy is to satisfy their guests in every way they can. 
