<Content>Great Hotel, Fab Location, Poor Service We stayed here for my birthday this month.The hotel is lovely looking, is in a great location and is pretty grand (although fairly over the top, reminded me of the Venetian in Vegas!). The gym is a total bonus and the terrace up there is lovely. Plus we had a great night's sleep on the 5th floor (it was very peaceful).The one thing that lets the place down is the service. There is always a queue to check in or check out (even late in the evening). Similarly a queue to see the concierge (who was not a cheery soul). Worst was the room service (they call it Service Express). My boyfriend had requested 4 days before arrival that flowers and wine be in our room upon arrival for a birthday surprise (very sweet of him!). They weren't there upon arrival. They weren't there after a prompting 'phone call. They took 5 hours after check in to arrive. And then it was separately. And when we had our Do Not Disturb sign illuminated- and were actually about to siesta. The message to accompany the flowers never arrived. The flowers were in an oasis stand, not a bouquet (as had been requested). And when we rang down for an iron it didn't arrive. So after 45 minutes (as we were getting late to leave) we rang again. Then we were told that they had run out. But no-one had bothered to call us. This is poor service. And it is frustrating because it is something that much cheaper hotels can, and do, get right. I think it is just lazy management (W hotel in NYC does not have these problems according to my boyfriend).I would recommend the hotel, but would warn you to be very wary of room service. We should have demanded that they waive the cost of the flowers. But we didn't as we were late (because of queueing for ages at the check-out, and because it is the kind of thing that sours a holiday). 
