<Author>aliNewJersey
<Content>everthing was perfect we stayed for 6 nights at the palace, and it was a superb week. we arrived early and were given our accomodation within one hour. we had upgraded on line thru the starwood plan to a suite prior to our arrival. the suite was lovely (not hugh by american standards) but perfect for my, myself and our 16 year old son. there are no pull out couches so you must pay 50 euros a night for a rollaway. our daughter (who is studying in madrid) decided to join us and they immediately sent another rollaway bed (at an extra 50 euros ) to the suite. the suite was perfect for 2 adults and 2 teenage children. the bathroom was beautiful and big and the shower was amazing!any requests we had over the phone for housekeeping (more towels, ice bucket) were filled within 2 minutes of a request. you need ice 24 hours a day in 99 degree weather. and they would bring ice upon request at no charge. the a/c in the hotel rooms was the best i felt in all of madrid!!the hotel went above and beyond to help us with anythng we requested and you must get the buffet bkfst included, its great but expensive. even if you just have coffee its so nice to sit there in the rotunda of the hotel, what a gorgeous hotel, gets my 5 stars of approval. this is an expensive hotel but it is worth it. 
