<Content>Pretty Impressive We stayed at the Westin for three days over Easter and can heartily recommend this hotel. Our room was a grand deluxe, a sort of mini-suite with a separate living area and a large bathroom. Everything was perfectly nice and in good working order, though the style/decor was a bit bland. We were particularly impressed that they supply four full size bath towels each day! The main downside is that we are the far end of this enormous hotel, meaning a very long walk back to reception. On the whole staff at the front desk and the breakfast buffet were helpful if not particularly friendly. Turn-down and housekeeping were both very efficient and discreet. The only disappointment arose from a confusion over inclusive breakfast. Guest services told us that we could take this in our room, but it turned out that they should have told us continental breakfast only. When we complained at a 鈧?0 bill, they took the breakfast away again. Such a waste and a petty attitude to customer service given that it was there mistake in the first place. Still, the buffet breakfast turned out to be well worth the effort of going downstairs.Location is excellent. I would also recommend the car service to and from the airport at a very reasonable 鈧?2. 
