<Content>Great hotel experience Stayed 5 nights in early January 2004 in this wonderful palace hotel. I can definitely agree with most of the positive feedback given by other previous reviewers. The hotel's location and facilities are without doubt superb. And as one reviewer previously said, its nice to be back in one's own palace at the end of each day after visiting others in the city. Scrumptious breakfast under the dome each morning was a wonderful experience. The breakfast staff was very friendly, especially one female staff - who, without prompting, gave me an insiders' tips on trips to, and places to visit, eat and shop in, Segovia and Toledo and who remembered my breakfast beverage preference on a daily basis, without being reminded (I strongly recommend the hot chocolate!). When I initially had problems with the hot water in my room on my first day I was immediately upgraded to another room with apologies but without question and, as I have already unpacked, the reception arranged for the cheerful maid service to repack everything (item by item) and transfer them to the other room! What level of service! I just wish the doorman would smile - that would make the hotel perfect. 
